node.text: So like 700 sensitive people called the FDA and they’re so mad at me for no reason 😂😂😂 They called me threatening to take my plane and take me to court and everything over this video. I never realized plane enthusiasts were so sensitive. So what am I going to do about it? Well….. I’m about to upload that soon 💀 Enjoy you dimly witted anti brain plane enthusiasts that don’t want me to learn how to fly 👻

node.text: Got a bigger bank for my birthday that understands how the world actually works. It’s funny how it went from “You’ll never be anything” to “Money changed you” in just 128 weeks. Except my mindset didn’t relate with those people when I had nothing, and it still doesn’t relate today. I screenshotted that comment years ago so I could use it to push me to do better. And to remind everyone now that no matter where you’re at, or what you’re doing, people will hate you. You just have to use it as fuel! I’m 23 years behind schedule so back to work.

node.text: I’m gonna be straight up with you all I’m half a million into this truck now and it’s not exactly easy 💀 I think we’re like half done. Anything bought today goes towards getting the worlds largest truck on the road. Yes the road.... Then I think I’m going to use this one for more than 7 months because it’s almost impossible to build anything bigger 😂 Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by WHISTLINDIESEL on June 28, 2021 tagging @dansdieselperformance, and @ddpaddy.

node.text: Monstermax 2 is officially halfway done!!!! Reminder that this is as low as the truck can possibly go on bumpstops. It goes much.... much higher 😂 Once everything is mocked up it’ll go into some testing to make sure everything works. Once we know it’ll work, and find the proper gear ratio it goes to @dansdieselperformance to get both LBZ engines completely gone through and tuned accordingly. Id like to push 1,000hp each for 2,000 total hp. I feel like that’s a safe number for a low gear ratio since it’ll be TORQUE AF. Do any haters wanna come out of the woodwork yet? Or are you officially all gone? Huge shoutout to @ddpaddy team for grinding on this massive project.
